<script>
$(document).ready(function() {
  $('a[href*="#access"]:not([href="#"])').click(function() {
    if (location.pathname.replace(/^\//,'') == this.pathname.replace(/^\//,'') && location.hostname == this.hostname) {
      var target = $(this.hash);
      target = target.length ? target : $('[name=' + this.hash.slice(1) +']');
      if (target.length) {
        $('html, body').animate({
          scrollTop: target.offset().top
        }, 1000);

        // $('#stocks').hide(0).fadeIn(100).removeClass('hidden');
        
        return false;
      }
    }
  });
  $('a[href*="#concerns"]:not([href="#"])').click(function() {
    if (location.pathname.replace(/^\//,'') == this.pathname.replace(/^\//,'') && location.hostname == this.hostname) {
      var target = $(this.hash);
      target = target.length ? target : $('[name=' + this.hash.slice(1) +']');
      if (target.length) {
        $('html, body').animate({
          scrollTop: target.offset().top
        }, 1000);

        
        return false;
      }
    }
  });

  $('#moreConcerns').click(function() {
    $('#moreConcernsField').removeClass('hiddendiv');
    $('#moreConcernsField').focus();
    $('#none').hide();
    $('#moreConcerns').hide();
  });
});

  </script>

<div class="edu-block">
  <div class="headline">
    Investing in the stock market is best over a long period of time (e.g. 20 years). But you may need to access your money in a shorter timeframe. 
    </div>
    <div class="big-headline">
    Do you want to know more about what would happen if you need to access your money sooner?
    </div>

    <br /><a href="#access" class="next-button">Yes</a><br /><br />
    <%= form_for @guest_user, url: wizard_path, method: :put do |f| %>
      <%= f.hidden_field :curious_about_access_to_money, value: "No" %>
    <%= f.submit "No", class:"next-button" %>
  <% end %>
</div>


<div id="access"><a name="access"></a>
  <div class="edu-block"> 
    <div class="big-headline">What happens if I need to access the money I invest sooner than 20 years?</div>

    <div class="headline">
    <p class="edu-para">You can pull your money out of the stock market at any time with no fees. If your investment is worth more at the time of selling than what you initially invested, you will owe some tax on the amount it went up (this is called "capital gains"). And you'll have the money in your bank account 4-6 days after initiating the sale. </p>
    <p class="edu-para">The main thing to note is that the stock market goes up and down over the years. If you need to access your money when the stock market is down, you may have less money than what you invested.</p>
    <br />
    <a href="#concerns" class="next-button">Continue</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="concerns"><a name="concerns"></a>
  <div class="edu-block"> 
    Any remaining concerns about accessing your money?
    <br /><br />
    <div id="none">
      <%= form_for @guest_user, url: wizard_path, method: :put do |f| %>
        <%= f.hidden_field :curious_about_access_to_money, value: "Yes" %> 
        <%= f.submit "Nope, I'm good to go!", class: "short-option-button" %>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <input type="button" id="moreConcerns" class="short-option-button" value="Yeah, actually...">
    <br />
    <div id="moreConcernsField" class="hiddendiv">
      <%= form_for @guest_user, url: wizard_path, method: :put do |f| %>
        <%= f.hidden_field :curious_about_access_to_money, value: "Yes" %>
        <%= f.text_area :remaining_concerns_about_access, :class=>"custom-text-area" %>
        <br /><br />
        <%= f.submit "Onwards", class:"next-button" %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>